      {
        "title": "CAQM reviews enforcement actions, inspections & compliance status NCR",
        "summary": "The Commission for Air Quality Management in NCR and Adjoining Areas today reviewed enforcement actions, inspections and compliance status across the National Capital Region. The Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change said that the 134th meeting of the Enforcement Task Force of CAQM reviewed actions between the 14th and 30th of last month. It […]",
        "article": "The Commission for Air Quality Management in NCR and Adjoining Areas today reviewed enforcement actions, inspections and compliance status across the National Capital Region. The Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change said that the 134th meeting of the Enforcement Task Force of CAQM reviewed actions between the 14th and 30th of last month. It noted that the Flying Squads of the Commission carried out 173 inspections during the period. Based on the inspection reports for the violations, closure of four units and projects, sealing of 27 DG sets, issuance of six orders for compliance and imposition of Environmental Compensation in 17 cases have been proposed. The task force also reviewed actions taken pursuant to the 133rd ETF meeting and noted that all actionable cases have been acted upon by the concerned agencies. It noted that the Flying Squads of the Commission have inspected over 27 thousand units and projects so far. Based on these inspections, over one thousand nine hundred Closure Directions have been issued, of which one thousand four hundred Resumption Orders have been issued upon verification of compliance. Further, 123 cases have been transferred to the respective State Pollution Control Boards and Delhi Pollution Control Committee for final decision, while 255 entities remain under examination for issuance of Resumption Orders.",
        "date": "2026-07-06",
        "pubDate": "2026-07-06T15:30:56+00:00",
        "link": "https://newsonair.gov.in/caqm-reviews-enforcement-actions-inspections-compliance-status-ncr/",
        "image_url": "",
        "image_credit": "",
        "source": "Prasar Bharati"
      },
      {
        "title": "125th birth anniversary of Dr Syama Prasad Mookerjee: PM Modi says his vision continues to guide modern India",
        "summary": "Prime Minister Narendra Modi has said that Dr Syama Prasad Mookerjee was a great patriot and a visionary dedicated to the integrity of India. In his video message on the occasion of the 125th birth anniversary of Dr Mookerjee, Mr Modi said, the thought of Dr Mookerjee is playing a major role in guiding modern […]",
        "article": "Prime Minister Narendra Modi has said that Dr Syama Prasad Mookerjee was a great patriot and a visionary dedicated to the integrity of India. In his video message on the occasion of the 125th birth anniversary of Dr Mookerjee, Mr Modi said, the thought of Dr Mookerjee is playing a major role in guiding modern India. Reflecting on the enduring legacy of the revered leader, the Prime Minister noted how the foundational thoughts planted decades ago are now visibly blossoming across the societal and political landscape. He credited this robust ideological framework with playing an indispensable role in charting the course for the nation&#8217;s contemporary progress. He said, Dr Mookerjee fiercely opposed the talk of two constitutions, two prime ministers, nd two flags in the country. The Prime Minister said Syama Prasad Mookerjee understood very well that the essence of nation-building is in the building of institutions. He said, Dr Mookerjee laid the foundation for such national institutions, which became India&#8217;s economic strength for decades to come. Mr Modi said, when there is a government with the resolution of Nation First, then national heroes also get due respect. He expressed immense pride that the current administration successfully honored the legacy of Dr Mookerjee by permanently dismantling the barriers of Article 370. Exploring the economic foresight of independent India&#8217;s first Industry Minister Dr Mookerjee, Mr Modi cataloged the establishment of monumental entities like Chittaranjan Locomotive Works, Sindri Fertiliser Plant, Damodar Valley Corporation, and IFCI. He credited these foundational institutions with successfully powering the nation&#8217;s railway, agricultural, energy, and financial sectors for decades. He said the government is celebrating the 125th birth anniversary of Dr Syama Prasad Mookerjee with a two-year national celebration. The Prime Minister said, this celebration began on July 6th of last year and will continue until July 6th of next year. He said, Dr Mukherjee&#8217;s life is an inspiration for the culmination of an idea to a mass movement. Mr Modi said, with the formation of the BJP government in Bengal, the state is adding enthusiasm to this national honour and commemorating this inspirational figure. Directing a powerful call to action toward the younger generation, the Prime Minister urged them to elevate the historical fight for a unified nation into a modern crusade for supreme national excellence. He challenged the youth to collectively shoulder the massive responsibility of achieving complete self-reliance. &nbsp;",
        "date": "2026-07-06",
        "pubDate": "2026-07-06T15:15:07+00:00",
        "link": "https://newsonair.gov.in/125th-birth-anniversary-of-dr-syama-prasad-mookerjee-pm-modi-says-his-thought-is-playing-major-role-in-guiding-modern-india/",
        "image_url": "",
        "image_credit": "",
        "source": "Prasar Bharati"
      },
      {
        "title": "Change of Guard in Shri Ram Janmabhoomi Teerth Kshetra Trust amid donation embezzlement case",
        "summary": "The Shri Ram Janmabhoomi Teerth Kshetra Trust today accepted the resignations of General Secretary Champat Rai and Trust member Dr Anil Mishra. Both had stepped down after their names surfaced in the alleged Ram Temple donation embezzlement case. Krishna Mohan has been appointed as the Interim General Secretary until a new General Secretary […]",
        "article": "The Shri Ram Janmabhoomi Teerth Kshetra Trust today accepted the resignations of General Secretary Champat Rai and Trust member Dr Anil Mishra. Both had stepped down after their names surfaced in the alleged Ram Temple donation embezzlement case. Krishna Mohan has been appointed as the Interim General Secretary until a new General Secretary is appointed. His complaint formed the basis of the FIR registered in the alleged donation irregularities case, following which eight people were arrested. The Trust has also decided to appoint a Chief Executive Officer (CEO). A three-member committee has been constituted to recommend suitable names and submit its suggestions for the appointment. During the meeting, the name of Gopal Nagar Kote was also removed from the list of the Trust&#8217;s special invitees. After the meeting, Trust Treasurer Govind Dev Giri and newly appointed Interim General Secretary Krishna Mohan addressed a press conference. Speaking to the media, Govind Dev Giri said that the possibility of a conspiracy behind the entire episode could not be ruled out. The Trust also displayed donated ornaments and other valuable items, asserting that all donated articles are safe and properly accounted for. It said that anyone can obtain details of the donated items from the Trust. Krishna Mohan acknowledged that the controversy had damaged the image of the Trust. However, in its official press release, the Trust stated that crores of Ram devotees continue to have unwavering faith in the Ram Temple and that there has been no decline in the number of pilgrims visiting the temple since the alleged donation embezzlement case came to light.",
        "date": "2026-07-06",
        "pubDate": "2026-07-06T14:48:26+00:00",
        "link": "https://newsonair.gov.in/change-of-guard-in-shri-ram-janmabhoomi-teerth-kshetra-trust-amid-donation-embezzlement-case/",
        "image_url": "",
        "image_credit": "",
        "source": "Prasar Bharati"
      }
